Supertest is a Node.js library for testing HTTP servers with a fluent API. Here's a basic example:
javascript
const request = require('supertest');
const app = require('./your-express-app');

describe('GET /user', () => {
  it('responds with JSON', async () => {
    const response = await request(app)
      .get('/user')
      .expect('Content-Type', /json/)
      .expect(200);
  });
});

You can chain methods like `.expect()` to validate responses, or drop down to the lower-level SuperAgent API for more control.
